templateAssets.content: THE ARTICULATION AGREEMENT BELOW IS SUBJECT TO PERIODIC REVISION. PLEASE CONSULT A COUNSELOR EVERY SEMESTER TO OBTAIN CURRENT INFORMATION ABOUT POSSIBLE CHANGES IN THE AGREEMENT.

This agreement primarily displays only the lower-division courses required in the major, and a few featured upper-division courses. Although completion of the coursework below is not necessarily mandatory prior to admission, students are strongly advised to complete as much lower division course preparation as possible prior to transfer. This agreement does not contain most upper-division (junior-senior) major requirements, course pre-requisites, general education or all-university coursework necessary for completion of this degree. In some cases, there may be alternative course options at the upper-division level. REFER TO THE FRESNO STATE CATALOG FOR FURTHER INFORMATION: http://www.fresnostate.edu/catalog/

The following are Business Administration Major Options:

  • Business Administration - Accelerated Option, B.S. - Continuing & Global Education
  • Business Administration - Accountancy Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Computer Information Systems Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Data Analytics Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Entrepreneurship Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Finance Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Human Resource Management Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - International Business Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Logistics & Supply Chain Strategies Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Management Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Marketing Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Real Estate & Urban Land Economics Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Special Option, B.S.
  • Business Administration - Sports Marketing Option, B.S.


All business students entering Fresno State are considered Pre-Business majors and are coded as such. In order to select an option in business and enroll in upper division business courses, pre-business students must do the following:

  • Complete IS 52 and 52L or equivalent course(s) with a grade of "C" or better or achieve a passing score on the Craig School of Business computer competency waiver examination. Please call the Craig School of Business Advising Center at 559-278-4943 for more information.
  • Complete the following courses or their equivalents with a grade of "C" or better in each course: ACCT 4A, ACCT 4B, BA 18, DS 71, DS 73, ECON 40 (or AGBS 1), and ECON 50.
  • Accountancy Option students must obtain a 2.5 between ACCT 4A and 4B.
  • Have a cumulative grade point average of at least 2.25 ("C" average).
  • General Education, Additional University Graduation Requirements, and Upper-division Writing courses can be double counted with major requirements.
  • These courses include BA 105W to fulfill the Upper-division Writing requirement, MKTG 100S to fulfill the AUGR M/I Requirement, DS 71 for GE Area 2, and ECON 50 for GE Area 4B. See advisor for details.
  • Additional University Graduation Requirements (9 units) - 
  • Accountancy majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Computer Information Systems majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Data Analytics majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Entrepreneurship majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Finance majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Human Resource Management majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • International Business majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Logistics & Supply Chain Strategies majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Management majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Marketing majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Real Estate & Urban Land Economics majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Sports Marketing majors are exempt from 3 units of this requirement
  • Submit a request to declare an option in business. Students may obtain this request form from the Craig School of Business Advising Center Office located in the Peters Bldg. Room 185 or call at 559-278-4943.Students may apply for an option in the semester during which they will complete all work needed for enrollment qualification in upper-division business courses. Approval will be contingent upon satisfactory fulfillment of the lower-division course prerequisites and the GPA standard; international (foreign) students must achieve a minimum score of 500 on the TOEFL exam.Transfer students will need to have their transcripts screened to see if they will receive equivalent credit for the above prerequisite courses. Transfer students must submit a complete set of transcripts (official or unofficial) or grade reports of all college-level study to the Craig School of Business Advising Center, 5245 N Backer Ave M/S PB 7, Fresno, CA 93740-8001 for evaluation. If you are transferring from out of the region, having a copy of the catalog(s) and course syllabi from the different colleges you attended will also be required. Upon receipt of these materials, transfer students' records will be evaluated. Notification of business course credit will then be sent by e-mail.Students who are ready to enroll in upper-division business courses, but who lack one or two of the pre-business courses, should contact the Craig School of Business Advising Center in Peters Building (PB), Room 185 for further information.

A grade of "C" or better must be earned for each course used to satisfy the requirements for the major.

Additional University Graduation Requirements


The Additional University Graduation Requirements are designed to complement the GE requirements. It is the policy of Fresno State, that all students will cultivate and refine their affective, cognitive, and physical faculties through studying great works of the human imagination; be equipped for lifelong understanding and development of themselves as integrated physiological, social, and psychological beings; and be prepared to understand and live in a multicultural and international world through their undergraduate education.

This will be accomplished through a total of 9 units from the following areas, each requiring 3 units:

  1. Arts/Humanities (A/H) - All students are required to take an Arts/Humanities course to graduate at the bachelor’s degree level. 
  2. Lifelong-Understanding and Self-Development (L/S) - All students are required to take a lifelong understanding and self-development course to for graduate at the bachelor’s degree level. 
  3. Multicultural/International (M/I) - All Students are required to take a Multicultural / International course at Fresno State to graduate at the bachelor’s degree level.
